Narrator: I entered the palace's residential...
en


I entered the palace's residential wing and began making my way to my quarters.

LineNo: 15857311,

Narrator: As I neared Vina's door, I thought...
en


As I neared Vina's door, I thought I heard her speaking to someone.

LineNo: 15857413,

Narrator: I was about to step closer when I f...
en


I was about to step closer when I felt a hand on my shoulder.

LineNo: 15857515,

Pabel Adria: Your Majesty! There you are.
en


"Your Majesty! There you are."

LineNo: 15857617,

Pabel Adria: I'm afraid there's an urgent matte...
en


"I'm afraid there's an urgent matter regarding wedding seating arrangements. This way, please."

LineNo: 15857719,

Narrator: Titus shadowed us as Pabel steered...
en


Titus shadowed us as Pabel steered me back down the hall towards my study.

LineNo: 15858123,

Player_Romus: Seating arrangements? Is that a eu...
en


"Seating arrangements? Is that a euphemism for something?"

LineNo: 15858225,

Player_Romus: I need to check in on Vina.
en


"I need to check in on Vina."

LineNo: 15858597,

Player_Romus: This had better be quick.
en


"This had better be quick."

LineNo: 15858699,

Player_Romus: Can't you figure it out yourself?
en


"Can't you figure it out yourself?"

LineNo: 15858801,

Pabel Adria: I've been trying.
en


"I've been trying."

LineNo: 15858903,

Pabel Adria: It will be. Hopefully.
en


"It will be. Hopefully."

LineNo: 15859005,

Narrator: He shook his head briskly and withd...
en


He shook his head briskly and withdrew a seating diagram from his breast pocket.

LineNo: 15859107,

Pabel Adria: This will only be a moment.
en


"This will only be a moment."

LineNo: 15859209,

Narrator: He withdrew a seating diagram from...
en


He withdrew a seating diagram from his breast pocket.

LineNo: 15859311,

Pabel Adria: At table 12, we have delegations f...
en


"At table 12, we have delegations from Agard, Qinal, the Free Cities and Nahrburk."

LineNo: 15859413,

Pabel Adria: Our guests from Qinal and the Free...
en


"Our guests from Qinal and the Free Cities refuse to sit next to each other or directly across from one another."

LineNo: 15859515,

Pabel Adria: The Qinali, meanwhile, would like...
en


"The Qinali, meanwhile, would like to sit directly to the left of our guest from Nahrburk, who in turn has asked to sit across from the Agardian."

LineNo: 15859641,

Player_Romus: Easy. Going clockwise, it's Agard,...
en


"Easy. Going clockwise, it's Agard, Qinal, Nahrburk, Free Cities."

LineNo: 15859743,

Player_Romus: Right. How about Free Cities, Nahr...
en


"Right. How about Free Cities, Nahrburk, Agard, Qinal?"

LineNo: 15859845,

Player_Romus: From the top of the table, it's Na...
en


"From the top of the table, it's Narhburk, Qinal, Agard, Free Cities."

LineNo: 15859947,

Player_Romus: I have no idea. Ask someone else.
en


"I have no idea. Ask someone else."

LineNo: 15860049,

Pabel Adria: Perfect. Thank you.
en


"Perfect. Thank you."

LineNo: 15860151,

Narrator: Pabel made a note.
en


Pabel made a note.

LineNo: 15860349,

Pabel Adria: I'm sorry, Your Majesty. I was afr...
en


"I'm sorry, Your Majesty. I was afraid of causing an international scandal."

LineNo: 15860451,

Pabel Adria: This must be a very emotional time...
en


"This must be a very emotional time for you. I still remember Her Highness' birth celebrations."

LineNo: 15860577,

Pabel Adria: I'm afraid there's an urgent matte...
en


"I'm afraid there's an urgent matter regarding the seating arrangements for tomorrow's diplomatic luncheon. This way please."

LineNo: 15860957,

Player_Romus: That just means you're getting old...
en


"That just means you're getting old, Pabel."

LineNo: 15861337,

Player_Romus: There's nothing romantic about tom...
en


"There's nothing romantic about tomorrow. It's a political event, nothing more."

LineNo: 15861439,

Player_Romus: I still have the congratulatory ci...
en


"I still have the congratulatory cigar you gave me. You must have saved up for it for months."

LineNo: 15861541,

Player_Romus: All sparrows have to leave the nes...
en


"All sparrows have to leave the nest sometime."

LineNo: 15861643,

Narrator: I detected a slight nervous quiver...
en


I detected a slight nervous quiver in his voice.

LineNo: 15861761,

Narrator: From just down the hall, I heard th...
en


From just down the hall, I heard the sound of barking. Bruno.

LineNo: 15861879,

Player_Romus: Huh. You were there?
en


"Huh. You were there?"

LineNo: 15862259,

Pabel Adria: Lespia's finest. The import taxes...
en


"Lespia's finest. The import taxes were horrendous."

LineNo: 15862361,

Pabel Adria: I was serving just beneath the hea...
en


"I was serving just beneath the head butler at the time."

LineNo: 15862463,

Player_Romus: Was this really such an urgent mat...
en


"Was this really such an urgent matter?"

LineNo: 15862565,

Player_Romus: I have to go.
en


"I have to go."

LineNo: 15862667,

Player_Romus: Pabel, where is Vina?
en


"Pabel, where is Vina?"

LineNo: 15862769,

Pabel Adria: No, I suppose it wasn't. Forgive m...
en


"No, I suppose it wasn't. Forgive me for wasting your time."

LineNo: 15862871,

Pabel Adria: Very well. I've gotten all your cl...
en


"Very well. I've gotten all your clothes ready for tomorrow."

LineNo: 15862973,

Pabel Adria: She's been in her room this entire...
en


"She's been in her room this entire time."

LineNo: 15863075,

Narrator: I rushed back down the hallway to V...
en


I rushed back down the hallway to Vina's room. Bruno was standing there, barking in front of a wide-open door.

LineNo: 15863455,

Narrator: I rushed back down the hallway to V...
en


I rushed back down the hallway to Vina's room. Her door was wide open.

LineNo: 15863557,

Narrator: I went inside and saw that the wind...
en


I went inside and saw that the window was open as well. My mother was standing in front of it, her face pale as a sheet.

LineNo: 15863675,

Player_Romus: WHERE IS SHE?!
en


"WHERE IS SHE?!"

LineNo: 15863777,

Player_Romus_Italic: I looked out the window at the pala...
en


I looked out the window at the palace gardens below. Nobody was there.

LineNo: 15863783,

Player_Romus_Italic: I looked out the window at the pala...
Menu Text en


Look out the window.

LineNo: 15863885,

Player_Romus: Did you let her run away?
en


"Did you let her run away?"

LineNo: 15863993,

Estela Toras: I... I don't know.
en


"I... I don't know."

LineNo: 15864095,

Estela Toras: No, of course not!
en


"No, of course not!"

LineNo: 15864197,

Estela Toras: I... I have no idea what happened.
en


"I... I have no idea what happened."

LineNo: 15864299,

Estela Toras: I came here to give her some mothe...
en


"I came here to give her some motherly advice ahead of her wedding. I opened the door, and she was gone."

LineNo: 15864981,

Player_Romus: We're hosting a diplomatic luncheo...
en


"We're hosting a diplomatic luncheon?"

LineNo: 15865083,

Pabel Adria: Apparently, yes.
en


"Apparently, yes."

LineNo: 15865185,

Estela Toras: I knew she'd been feeling down lat...
en


"I knew she'd been feeling down lately, so I came to check up on her. I opened the door, and she was gone."

LineNo: 15865311,

Player_Romus: You're lying. I heard her talking...
en


"You're lying. I heard her talking to someone in there."

LineNo: 15865413,

Player_Romus: TITUS! FIND HER!
en


"TITUS! FIND HER!"

LineNo: 15865515,

Player_Romus: She can't have gone far. The palac...
en


"She can't have gone far. The palace grounds are under heavy security."

LineNo: 15865617,

Narrator: Titus spoke into his radio. I strug...
en


Titus spoke into his radio. I struggled to make out the words on the other end.

LineNo: 15865719,

Titus Gordion: I'm already on it, Your Majesty.
en


"I'm already on it, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15865821,

Titus Gordion: I'm communicating with my fellow g...
en


"I'm communicating with my fellow guards now, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15865923,

Player_Romus: If she didn't want to get married,...
en


"If she didn't want to get married, she could have just told me."

LineNo: 15866025,

Player_Romus: If she wasn't happy, she could hav...
en


"If she wasn't happy, she could have just told me."

LineNo: 15866127,

Estela Toras: She did tell you, Romus.
en


"She did tell you, Romus."

LineNo: 15866229,

Estela Toras: Interesting. Perhaps she was on th...
en


"Interesting. Perhaps she was on the phone."

LineNo: 15866331,

Estela Toras: She did tell you, Romus.
en


"She did tell you, Romus."

LineNo: 15866433,

Titus Gordion: I've received word that one of my...
en


"I've received word that one of my men left his shift early just now. He was complaining of indigestion."

LineNo: 15866535,

Player_Romus: Track him down. See that he gets w...
en


"Track him down. See that he gets what's coming to him."

LineNo: 15866637,

Player_Romus: You have to find him, Titus. I wan...
en


"You have to find him, Titus. I want my daughter back."

LineNo: 15866739,

Player_Romus: So she had an accomplice. I though...
en


"So she had an accomplice. I thought you Golden Guards were incorruptible."

LineNo: 15866841,

Titus Gordion: I tried to reach him, but he's alr...
en


"I tried to reach him, but he's already turned his radio off."

LineNo: 15867237,

Player_Romus: It's that easy for someone to esca...
en


"It's that easy for someone to escape the palace?!"

LineNo: 15867339,

Estela Toras: Everybody has a weakness, darling....
en


"Everybody has a weakness, darling. Even Captain Gordion here."

LineNo: 15867441,

Narrator: Titus cleared his throat.
en


Titus cleared his throat.

LineNo: 15867543,

Titus Gordion: I'll try my best, Your Majesty.
en


"I'll try my best, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 15867645,

Titus Gordion: Your Majesty, Palas Rezna's securi...
en


"Your Majesty, Palas Rezna's security systems are designed to keep intruders out. Not to keep princesses in."

LineNo: 15867747,

Titus Gordion: Right now, the goal is getting Pri...
en


"Right now, the goal is getting Princess Vina back. We can discuss the particulars later."

LineNo: 15867849,

Titus Gordion: I'm going to talk to the guards at...
en


"I'm going to talk to the guards at the gates. See if I can find out more."

LineNo: 15868047,

Narrator: He dashed out, leaving me alone wit...
en


He dashed out, leaving me alone with my mother.

LineNo: 15868173,

Player_Romus: Pabel had a hand in this, didn't h...
en


"Pabel had a hand in this, didn't he? Where did he go?"

LineNo: 15868275,

Player_Romus: Seriously, Mother. Did you help he...
en


"Seriously, Mother. Did you help her escape?"

LineNo: 15868647,

Player_Romus: Tell me where she is, or I'll tell...
en


"Tell me where she is, or I'll tell everyone you're a Dastnurist."

LineNo: 15868749,

Player_Romus: What the hell am I supposed to do...
en


"What the hell am I supposed to do now?"

LineNo: 15868851,

Narrator: My mother shrugged.
en


My mother shrugged.

LineNo: 15868953,

Estela Toras: Your butler knows every nook and c...
en


"Your butler knows every nook and cranny of this palace, including the secret passageways. If he played any role in her escape, he's long gone by now."

LineNo: 15869055,

Estela Toras: How many times must I tell you? Sh...
en


"How many times must I tell you? She was already gone when I came in."

LineNo: 15869157,

Estela Toras: Go on, then. I honestly don't know.
en


"Go on, then. I honestly don't know."

LineNo: 15869259,

Estela Toras: You could track her down. But she'...
en


"You could track her down. But she'll only try to escape again."

LineNo: 15869735,

Estela Toras: Your real problem is telling the r...
en


"Your real problem is telling the rest of the continent that Rizia's big royal wedding is off."

LineNo: 15869869,

Estela Toras: Your real problem is explaining to...
en


"Your real problem is explaining to the international press that the Kingdom of Rizia can't hold on to its princesses."

LineNo: 15869987,

Estela Toras: If she did drive off with that gua...
en


"If she did drive off with that guard, they could have gone anywhere."

LineNo: 15870089,

Narrator: My mother shrugged.
en


My mother shrugged.

LineNo: 15870191,

Player_Romus: Shit. All that wartime sympathy, l...
en


"Shit. All that wartime sympathy, literally out the window."

LineNo: 15870293,

Narrator: There was pain in his eyes as he lo...
en


There was pain in his eyes as he looked at me.

LineNo: 15870673,

Pabel Adria: Good night, Romus. And good luck.
en


"Good night, Romus. And good luck."

LineNo: 15870775,

Player_Romus: This is just cold feet. She'll com...
en


"This is just cold feet. She'll come back eventually."

LineNo: 15870877,

Player_Romus: If Titus does manage to track her...
en


"If Titus does manage to track her down, I'll have her beheaded."

LineNo: 15871249,

Player_Romus: They'll make me look like a monste...
en


"They'll make me look like a monster."

LineNo: 15871351,

Player_Romus: This is just a tantrum. I'm sure s...
en


"This is just a tantrum. I'm sure she'll come back eventually."

LineNo: 15871723,

Player_Romus: And Hugo. What do I tell Hugo?
en


"And Hugo. What do I tell Hugo?"

LineNo: 15872103,

Player_Romus: And Axel. What do I tell Axel?
en


"And Axel. What do I tell Axel?"

LineNo: 15872205,

Player_Romus: This was all my fault. I should ha...
en


"This was all my fault. I should have listened to her."

Estela Toras: If she doesn't, it'll be the end o...
en


"If she doesn't, it'll be the end of our family's line of succession."

LineNo: 15872409,

Estela Toras: You tell him that the Rizia-Pales...
en


"You tell him that the Rizia-Pales reunion everyone's been waiting for will have to happen another way."

Estela Toras: You tell him that he's your new su...
en


"You tell him that he's your new successor."

LineNo: 15872613,

Estela Toras: If she doesn't, it'll be the end o...
en


"If she doesn't, it'll be the end of our family's line of succession."

LineNo: 15872715,

Estela Toras: Not to mention our family's line o...
en


"Not to mention our family's line of succession."

LineNo: 15872817,

Estela Toras: But perhaps that's a small price t...
en


"But perhaps that's a small price to pay for Her Highness' happiness."

Estela Toras: It's too late now. You can conside...
en


"It's too late now. You can consider this the end of our family's line of succession."

Estela Toras: If you do, that'll be the end of y...
en


"If you do, that'll be the end of your line of succession."

LineNo: 15873401,

Estela Toras: Unless...
en


"Unless..."

LineNo: 15873503,

Estela Toras: What's more, our family's line of...
en


"What's more, our family's line of succession will be most definitively over."

LineNo: 15873605,

Narrator: She sighed.
en


She sighed.

LineNo: 15873707,

Estela Toras: But perhaps that's a small price t...
en


"But perhaps that's a small price to pay for Her Highness' happiness."

LineNo: 15874087,

Estela Toras: Unless...
en


"Unless..."

LineNo: 15874189,

Narrator: She sighed.
en


She sighed.

Narrator: She slowly walked away, lost in tho...
en


She slowly walked away, lost in thought.
